Barcelona have released their squad to face Inter Milan in the UEFA Champions League fixture on Tuesday night in Italy. Barcelona manager, Ernesto Valverde dropped captain, Lionel Messi from his 20-man squad list to tackle the Serie A giant. Barcelona made this known in a tweet on their official Twitter page on Monday afternoon. Barca head to the game following a 5-2 victory over Mallorca in the La Liga over the weekend. Below is Barcelona’s squad against Mallorca: Ter Stegen, I. Rakitic, Sergio, Todibo, Suárez, Neto, Lenglet, M. Wague, Griezmann, Aleñá, Inaki Pena, F. De Jong, Vidal, Umtiti, Junior, Riqui Puig, Araujo, Carles Pérez, Ansu Fati, and Morer. The kick-off time for the match is 9 pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.